text: Winesap is an extinct town in Chelan County, in the U.S. state of Washington. The GNIS classifies it as a populated place. A post office called Winesap was established in 1909, and remained in operation until 1944. An early variant name was Coles View. ==References== Category:Ghost towns in Washington (state) Category:Geography of Chelan County, Washington
title: Winesap, Washington
